Bandits have launched fresh coordinated attacks on four communities in Kajuru Local Government Area, Kaduna State, killing over 32 persons and destroying several houses pf the locals. The communities were identified to include Ungwan Gamu, Dogon Noma, Ungwan Sarki and Maikori.  The destroyed houses were also said to include a Church building.
The bandits were said to have invaded Dogon Noma in the early hours of Sunday before moving  to invade Ungwan Gamu and Maikori communities, killing and burning houses.
